The prices of diesel and paraffin are also set to increase by 63c/litre and up to 76c/litre respectively. JOHANNESBURG - The Department of Energy has announced that the price of petrol will increase by 45 cents a litre from 2 November.Diesel will rise by 63 cents a litre and illuminating paraffin by up to 76 cents per litre.Illuminating paraffin is going up 57 cents, while there s a 59 cents hike per kilogramme of LP gas.Nedbank economist Issac Matshego said, At the moment we are seeing food prices being pressured by drought conditions. As a result, we expect the higher fuel prices to add to the inflationary pressure. Inflation is likely to remain above the six level for the next few months. 